problems.title: Missing Elements In Array
problems.description: Write a Java program to find missing elements in an array. Given an array of size `n` containing integers in the range `[1, n]`, find all the numbers in the range `[1, n]` that are not present in the array. Print them in increasing order separated by space.
problems.examples:
Sample Input
5
1 1 2 3 5

Sample Output
4

Sample Input
5
4 3 2 7 8 2 3 1

Sample Output
5 6
hintsList: Use a frequency array or a set to track present elements.
